UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. James Walter KING, Defendant-Appellant. No. 30826

Summary Calendar.*

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 8, 1971. J. Kennedy Hutcheson (court-appointed), Hutcheson, Forbes & Lassiter, Jacksonville, Fla., for defendant-appellant. John L. Briggs, U. S. Atty., Aaron K. Bowden, Asst. U. S. Atty., Jacksonville, Fla., for plaintiff-appellee.

Before WISDOM, COLEMAN and SIMPSON, Circuit Judges.

Rule 18, 5 Cir.; see Isbell Enterprises, Inc. v. Citizens Casualty Company of New York et al., 5 Cir. 1970, 431 F.2d 409, Part I.

 PER CURIAM:

Affirmed. See Local Rule 21.**

See N.L.R.B. v. Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, 5 Cir. 1970, 430 F.2d 966.
